\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Machine learning has revolutionized the field of predictive analytics by enabling algorithms to learn from and make predictions on data. It encompasses various techniques such as supervised learning, where the model is trained on a labeled dataset, and unsupervised learning, where the model identifies patterns in an unlabeled dataset. Key algorithms include neural networks, decision trees, and support vector machines. Applications of machine learning in predictive analytics are extensive, ranging from forecasting customer behavior to enhancing cybersecurity. Companies utilize machine learning models to predict trends, optimize operations, and personalize customer interactions, significantly improving decision-making processes.}